The published Docker image at `ghcr.io/xray-eval/xray` bundles a
number of third-party packages. Their copyright notices and license
terms are reproduced below, grouped by license class. The exhaustive
per-package list is reproducible from the committed lockfile via:

    pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
    pnpm licenses list --prod

`bun run license:check` verifies on every CI run that no production
dependency is under GPL-*, AGPL-*, or SSPL-*; the build fails if one
slips in.

---

## License classes currently present in the production dependency set

(Sourced from `pnpm licenses list --prod --json` against the
committed `pnpm-lock.yaml`. Last verified manually: see commit log.)

- **MIT** — the bulk of the runtime tree (React, Hono, Drizzle ORM,
  Radix UI primitives, TanStack Query / Router, valibot, ts-pattern,
  ky, tailwindcss, lucide-react, and roughly a hundred transitive
  dependencies).
- **Apache-2.0** — a small number of utility packages.
- **ISC** — a handful of small utilities.
- **0BSD** — one dependency.
- **Unlicense** — one dependency.
- **(MIT OR CC0-1.0)** — one dual-licensed dependency.
- **OFL-1.1** — `@fontsource-variable/jetbrains-mono` and
  `@fontsource-variable/onest`. See the per-font attribution below.

No production dependency is under a copyleft license (GPL, LGPL,
AGPL, SSPL, MPL, EPL, CDDL, CC-BY-SA, or EUPL) at the time of
writing.

