## Per-package attribution where the license requires it

### Fonts (SIL Open Font License 1.1)

Both bundled variable fonts ship under the SIL Open Font License,
Version 1.1 — <https://openfontlicense.org/open-font-license-official-text/>.
The OFL requires that the original copyright lines be preserved
when the fonts are redistributed.

- **JetBrains Mono** — Copyright (c) 2020, JetBrains s.r.o.
  (<https://www.jetbrains.com/>) with Reserved Font Name "JetBrains
  Mono". Source: <https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono>,
  packaged as `@fontsource-variable/jetbrains-mono`.

- **Onest** — Copyright (c) 2023, the Onest Project Authors
  (<https://github.com/RKDronel/Onest>). Packaged as
  `@fontsource-variable/onest`.

### All other categories (MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD / ISC / 0BSD /
Unlicense / CC0)

Each individual package preserves its own copyright header inside
`node_modules/<package>/LICENSE` (or equivalent). Those headers
travel with the source tree and are reproduced in the Docker image
under `/app/node_modules/`. Running

    pnpm licenses list --prod --long

prints every license file inline.

