## What changes here when a dependency is added or removed

1. Add the dependency via `pnpm add` (subject to the 7-day cooldown
   policy in `.claude/rules/supply-chain.md`).
2. Run `bun run license:check` locally. If the package's license is
   in the forbidden set, the script exits non-zero and the PR is
   blocked.
3. If the new license is a class not yet listed above (e.g. the first
   `BlueOak-1.0.0` dep), append it to the License-classes section
   above with the same wording as the others.
4. If the new package's license requires explicit attribution beyond
   "license file preserved in `node_modules`" — fonts, art assets,
   any package that ships a `NOTICE` of its own — append the
   attribution block to the per-package section above.

This file is not auto-generated; it is curated. The verification
script (`scripts/license-check.ts`) is what guards the dependency
set on every push.
